d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   One too Watch out for</span><hr size=1> I've probably let this bother me too much.But I still wanted to share this with everyone,The other night I made a stop in North Qeynos.I had some stuff leftover from Lake of Ill Omen.So did an /ooc Free weapon to the first Newbie who pokes me.I always appreciated it when someone did something like this and I was on the receiving end.So I try to keep the flow going.<br>
  Anyways this Ranger pokes me.He had no armor present,looked pretty new so I gave him a sheer blade I think it was.Nothing spectacular,like 6d/33dly.This Ranger then says watch this.I watch him put on peice after peice of Ivy Etched armor.Then says in /tell Hey this should go nice with this weapon huh?(he then put a Yak in the trade window along with a another high level 2 hand weapon).I responded &quot;I would not have given it too you at all,I would have given it too someone who actually could have used it.And wasnt twinked to the hilt&quot;.<br>
   He then starts trying to auction it off.Meanwhile hitting me with /tell &quot;Is that me?&quot; <br>
   It was just really bad form in my opinion.I let the guy get too me a little,I shouldnt have let it bother me.But it did kinda suck.Sooo you guys hunting in BB,QH,NQ,and the outlying areas.Watch out For a Guy named Tenany!! Stay away from him.I had grouped with him with my warrior in BB as well,He WILL!!! Leave you hanging if your group starts to get beat down!!! (when i did a check on who was in zone his Name came up as around level 14) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uaonedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aonedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/01 1:13:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: One too Watch out for</span><hr size=1> Man, that just sucks. I can't believe that someone would actually do something like that. What really sucks about it is that it will make you weary of giving stuff to newbies. Thanks for the info bud<br>
