<br>
When I want to give out stuff I dont do an ooc or auction.  I simply do a who all on the zone, unless I really dont care who gets it.  Then, I observe any possible takers on what I am giving out.  For example say I have a Langseax(warrior only weapon).   Id look for low lvl warriors in the zone who appear to be struggling in the equipment area.  After I find one, I send a tell to him/her.  <br>
<br>
Another way to be sure you arent giving things away to an ungreatful twinked son of a......  is observe them in their hunting enviornment.  They'll surely be fully equipped when out fighting, so you get no suprises.  <br>
<br>
It's kind of a lot to go through just to be handing out freebies; but by doing it this way it will be as fair as YOU want it to be, and you can be sure it gets to someone who needs it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ualzabomachera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alzabo Machera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/01 12:20:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible Solution</span><hr size=1> Ill keep that in mind Monarch thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uanathae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anathae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/01 1:57:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Possible Solution</span><hr size=1> hm... drive by twinkings <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
